729189f-a.title: Richmond: New Dorp Lane - South Railroad Avenue
729189f-a.text:
(1)
129 New Dorp Lane, north side, at the head of South Railroad
Avenue (formerly 6th Street), showing Gillies' Phoenix Hotel. It
was owned by M. S. Burbank in 1898. TThe view is westward.
August 2, 1929
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(2)
Another view, looking east across the Staten Island Railroad
tracks from North Railroad Avenue.
August 2, 1929
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
